{"parentUuid":"09646500-f824-4a9d-bad1-934f27f4a37b","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"a6867b8fa220460c5","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0158sjGy3yELYEced7HS8Vvd","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Qwen2.5-Coder-7B SWE-bench LiveCodeBench score 2024 vs Qwen3-8B coding benchmark\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Qwen2.5-Coder Technical Report\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2409.12186v3\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen2.5-Coder Series: Powerful, Diverse, Practical. | Qwen\",\"url\":\"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen2.5-coder-family/\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-Bench++: A Framework for the Scalable Generation of Software Engineering Benchmarks from Open-Source Repositories\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.17419\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen AI for Coding: Reviews, Usage and Performance in 2026 | Second Talent\",\"url\":\"https://www.secondtalent.com/resources/qwen-ai-for-coding-reviews-usage-and-performance/\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-bench Results Viewer\",\"url\":\"https://www.swebench.com/viewer.html\"},{\"title\":\"SWE-MERA: A Dynamic Benchmark for Agenticly Evaluating Large Language Models on Software Engineering Tasks\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2507.11059\"},{\"title\":\"CRPE: Expanding The Reasoning Capability of Large Language Model for Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.10594\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3-Coder-Next Technical Report\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.00729v1\"}]\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Qwen3 8B - Intelligence, Performance & Price Analysis\",\"url\":\"https://artificialanalysis.ai/models/qwen3-8b-instruct\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3: Think Deeper, Act Faster | Qwen\",\"url\":\"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen3/\"},{\"title\":\"2025-05-15 Qwen3 Technical Report Qwen Team https://huggingface.co/Qwen\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.09388\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3-8B - Model Info, Parameters, Benchmarks - SiliconFlow\\\"\",\"url\":\"https://www.siliconflow.com/models/qwen3-8b\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3.5 0.8B API Benchmarks: Latency, Throughput & Cost\",\"url\":\"https://deepinfra.com/blog/qwen-3-5-0-8b-via-deepinfra-api-benchmarks\"},{\"title\":\"Off-Trajectory Reasoning: Can LLMs Collaborate on Reasoning Trajectory?\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2510.06410\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3-VL Technical Report\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2511.21631\"},{\"title\":\"Qwen3 Coder Performance Evaluation: A Comparative Analysis Against Leading Models\",\"url\":\"https://eval.16x.engineer/blog/qwen3-coder-evaluation-results\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the coding benchmark performance:\n\n## Qwen2.5-Coder-7B Performance\n\nOn LiveCodeBench, the Qwen-2.5-Coder-7B-Instruct model achieved an impressive Pass@1 accuracy of 37.6%. The evaluation used the latest 4 months of LiveCodeBench (2024.07 - 2024.11) questions.\n\nFor SWE-bench scores, the Qwen2.5-Coder 32B version scores 69.6% on SWE-Bench Verified, though specific scores for the 7B model on SWE-Bench were not detailed in the search results.\n\n## Qwen3-8B Coding Performance\n\nQwen3-8B is the latest large language model in the Qwen series with 8.2B parameters and supports seamless switching between thinking mode (for complex logical reasoning, math, and coding) and non-thinking mode. It demonstrates significantly enhanced reasoning capabilities, surpassing previous QwQ and Qwen2.5 instruct models in mathematics, code generation, and commonsense logical reasoning.\n\nHowever, the search results did not provide specific LiveCodeBench or SWE-Bench numerical scores for the Qwen3-8B model. The results indicate that Qwen3-8B / 4B / 1.7B-Base models even outperform larger size Qwen2.5-14B / 7B / 3B Base models on over half of the benchmarks, especially on STEM-related and coding benchmarks.\n\nFor a direct numerical comparison of LiveCodeBench and SWE-Bench scores between these two models, additional sources would be needed.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"f2d7a877-63e0-4d9d-8354-0d7b6a2f1ca4","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:53.772Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Qwen2.5-Coder-7B SWE-bench LiveCodeBench score 2024 vs Qwen3-8B coding benchmark","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01PCSGh9cUaNFLikFTzA9ZJ6","content":[{"title":"Qwen2.5-Coder Technical Report","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2409.12186v3"},{"title":"Qwen2.5-Coder Series: Powerful, Diverse, Practical. | Qwen","url":"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen2.5-coder-family/"},{"title":"SWE-Bench++: A Framework for the Scalable Generation of Software Engineering Benchmarks from Open-Source Repositories","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.17419"},{"title":"Qwen AI for Coding: Reviews, Usage and Performance in 2026 | Second Talent","url":"https://www.secondtalent.com/resources/qwen-ai-for-coding-reviews-usage-and-performance/"},{"title":"SWE-bench Results Viewer","url":"https://www.swebench.com/viewer.html"},{"title":"SWE-MERA: A Dynamic Benchmark for Agenticly Evaluating Large Language Models on Software Engineering Tasks","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2507.11059"},{"title":"CRPE: Expanding The Reasoning Capability of Large Language Model for Code Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.10594"},{"title":"Qwen3-Coder-Next Technical Report","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.00729v1"}]},{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01RZRYCJTqmv2M8gAMUK7EEE","content":[{"title":"Qwen3 8B - Intelligence, Performance & Price Analysis","url":"https://artificialanalysis.ai/models/qwen3-8b-instruct"},{"title":"Qwen3: Think Deeper, Act Faster | Qwen","url":"https://qwenlm.github.io/blog/qwen3/"},{"title":"2025-05-15 Qwen3 Technical Report Qwen Team https://huggingface.co/Qwen","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.09388"},{"title":"Qwen3-8B - Model Info, Parameters, Benchmarks - SiliconFlow\"","url":"https://www.siliconflow.com/models/qwen3-8b"},{"title":"Qwen3.5 0.8B API Benchmarks: Latency, Through